726239f-c.text:
Broadway, at the N. E. corner of Vernon Boulevard. Mr. E. L. Armbruster states that this may be the Mayor Henry Debevoise House, but that controversy exists as to the authenticity of that. He also makes reference to T. Dusenbury's map No. 540,1882. C. W.
Strong was the owner i 1873.
View 1: Eugene L. Armbruster  May, 1923
Views 2,3: P. L. Sperr  March 9, 1931

726240f-c.text:
Broadway, at the N. E. corner of Vernon Boulevard, showing an old farmhouse, dating back to pre-Revolutionary days. Eugene L. Armbruster states that this may have been Mayor Henry Debevoise's house, but that some disagreement exists whether it actually was. It was owned by Miss Bragar in 1841, and by C. W. Strang in 1873.
P. Bartlett was the owner in 1896.
Views 1,2: May, 1923
Views 3,4: April, 1925
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
